    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-beef-in-black-bean-with-baked-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based, <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced beef</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-beef-in-black-bean-with-baked-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and chop into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[75ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and whisk it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>cornflour slurry</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-beef-in-black-bean-with-baked-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the beef has browned, add the <strong>onion wedges </strong>and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> to the pot with a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>black bean paste</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and put the dish in the oven and cook, covered, for an initial 25 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-beef-in-black-bean-with-baked-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-beef-in-black-bean-with-baked-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p><p>After the beef has had an initial 25 min, remove the dish from the oven and add the <strong>chopped pepper </strong>and <strong>cornflour slurry</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven and cook, covered, for a further 30 min or until the sauce has thickened and the beef is cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> one pot beef in black bean</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-beef-in-black-bean-with-baked-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 120ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked cauliflower rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-beef-in-black-bean-with-baked-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot beef in black bean </strong>with the <strong>baked cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
